The gubernatorial candidate of the People’s Democratic Party in the 2018 governorship election, Senator Ademola Adeleke has congratulated Governor Gboyega Oyetola on his victory at the Supreme Court. Adeleke in a press statement issued by his media aide, Olawale Rasheed after the court ruling earlier on Friday said his ambition to rule Osun was never a do or die affair. He said he accepted the verdict of the Supreme Court being the apex court in the land. OVER 5,000 NIGERIAN MEN HAVE  OVERCOME POOR BEDROOM PERFORMANCE SYNDROME DUE TO THIS BRILLIANT DISCOVERY. CLICK HERE TO KNOW MORE “Regardless of my disagreement and disappointment with it, the judgement remains the final. Thus, as a democrat and law-abiding citizen, I accept the ruling no matter my misgivings.” “I wish Governor Oyetola well in the governance of Osun state “, Senator Adeleke said. He expressed immense gratitude and appreciation to his teeming supporters, leaders and members of the Peoples Democratic Party for their massive support throughout the duration of the case, lauding “our high spirit and commitment to the cause of democracy which we championed from last year till date.” “In all circumstances, we must thank God Almighty. We gallantly fought a good fight in pursuance of a democratic cause. The ideals we fought for lives on.” Osun 2018: It is contest between APC, PDP Anxiety in Osun as S/Court decides Oyetola, Adeleke’s fate today Osun guber: Scores of judgement as Adeleke, Oyetola lock horns in courts Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin